RetailNova Sales SQL Analysis
This project uses SQL to analyze a retail business database. It involves creating shortcuts (indexes) for faster searching and writing queries to answer important business questions about sales, profit, and customer behavior.

What this project does:

Database Optimization: Creates indexes on customer IDs, product categories, and order dates to make queries run much faster.
Profit Tracking: Calculates exactly how much money the business makes on every order.
Top Performers: Identifies the top 5 customers who bring in the most profit.
Trend Analysis: Compares monthly profit across different regions over the last two years.
Product Health: Finds the top 3 most-returned products in every category to help improve quality.
Customer Loyalty: Calculates how long the most profitable customers have been shopping with the company.

Key SQL Skills Used:

Joins: Combining data from sales, products, stores, and customers.
Aggregations: Using SUM, COUNT, and AVG to summarize data.
Window Functions: Using ROW_NUMBER and RANK to find top items.
Date Functions: Filtering data by time and calculating customer tenure.
